  "prompt": "What does \"RIC\" mean with reference to email?",
  "response": "\"RIC\" in the context of email most commonly refers to **Read, Ignore, or Click**.\n\nIt's a shorthand way to describe the user's reaction to an email. Specifically, it's a method used to analyze email effectiveness and understand how recipients are engaging with the message.\n\nHere's a breakdown:\n\n*   **Read:** The recipient opened and read the email.\n*   **Ignore:** The recipient received the email but ignored it (didn't open, read, or interact). This could be due to a misleading subject line, irrelevant content, or the recipient simply being too busy.\n*   **Click:** The recipient opened the email and clicked on a link or call to action within the email. This indicates the highest level of engagement.\n\nBy tracking RIC, marketers and email senders can gain insights into:\n\n*   Subject line effectiveness (influences open rates and therefore Read rates)\n*   Content relevance (influences Read and Click rates)\n*   Call to action effectiveness (influences Click rates)\n*   Overall campaign performance\n\nWhile sometimes other meanings could be used depending on context, this is the most common use of RIC in email discussions.\n",
